Bring a large #pot{} of water to a rapid boil on high heat. Rinse the
@brown basmati rice{1/2%cup} under running water for half a minute. Add the
rice with @salt{1/4%tsp} to the water and cook on high heat for around
~{25%minutes} (topping up the water if you need to).

Drain and thoroughly rinse the @green lentils{1}. Peel and finely dice the
@onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel the @ginger{1}(peeled and finely chopped)
using the edge of a #spoon{} and then very finely chop (or grate it). Peel and
very finely dice the @garlic clove{1}. Chop the @green beans{1}(chopped widthways
into 3 pieces, disregarding the ends) widthways into 3 pieces, disregarding the
ends.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-low heat. Once warm add the
onion, ginger and garlic with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and slowly cook
for ~{5%minutes}.

Add the @panang curry paste{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} before adding the
@coconut milk{3/4%can}. Add half the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} with @water{100%ml}
and turn the heat to medium.

Separate the @cauliflower{2}(cut into florets) into bite size pieces and add
these and the green beans into the curry sauce. Put a #lid{} on the #pan{}
and let it gently bubble away for ~{10%minutes}, before removing the lid and
cooking for a further ~{5%minutes}.

Lastly chop a few tbsp of @coriander{3}(chopped) and stir both this and the
lentils through the curry before serving it on top of your brown rice.

